{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17507634","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17507634"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":1,"answeredAt":"2025-09-29T11:55:18+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-29T11:55:18+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"2652"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"2652","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/2652"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0.14,0.2,0.11,0.2,0.35]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"2652"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"35775"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"2652","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/2652"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"2652"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"20603"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"4"},{"type":"tags","id":"65"},{"type":"tags","id":"72"},{"type":"tags","id":"76"},{"type":"tags","id":"1144"},{"type":"tags","id":"1432"},{"type":"tags","id":"4962"},{"type":"tags","id":"4987"},{"type":"tags","id":"8218"},{"type":"tags","id":"11625"},{"type":"tags","id":"11650"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"3097"},{"type":"contributions","id":"3113"},{"type":"contributions","id":"3326"},{"type":"contributions","id":"16321"},{"type":"contributions","id":"42538"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"35775","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/35775"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EA 62-year-old man presents with a two week history of hoarseness of voice. He has not had any recent respiratory tract infections. He has a 25 pack-year smoking history. Physical examination reveals smooth enlargement of the lower pole of the right lobe of the thyroid.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThyroid function tests are normal. An ultrasound is arranged, which shows a 3cm solitary nodule in the right lobe of the thyroid. The remainder of the gland appears normal. An ultrasound-guided aspiration fine needle aspiration is inconclusive.\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following is the most appropriate next step investigation?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Thyroid scintigraphy","Repeat fine needle aspiration","CT neck","Radioactive iodine uptake test","Core needle biopsy"],"correctOptions":[1],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EThe sample gathered via fine needle aspiration (FNA) biopsy is used to determine cytology and is therefore essential in the evaluation of a thyroid nodule. However, non-diagnostic or unsatisfactory results are common (22%) and in such circumstances \u003Cstrong\u003Erepeat FNA\u003C/strong\u003E should be performed.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ECore needle biopsy\u003C/strong\u003E (CNB) involves a larger sample being taken from the thyroid. While some studies suggest CNB is more accurate than FNA, current recommendations in Australia support the use of FNA only.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ECT neck \u003C/strong\u003Eis used selectively for staging of known thyroid malignancy.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EThyroid scintigraphy\u003C/strong\u003E is nuclear imaging of the thyroid gland. It is used in patients with a low TSH, where increased uptake may suggest a hyperactive thyroid.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EA \u003Cstrong\u003Eradioactive iodine uptake test \u003C/strong\u003Eprovides a measure of thyroid gland activity - and that is not the information that is being sought in this case.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":null,"learningPoints":["Non-diagnostic or unsatisfactory fine needle aspiration of the thyroid should be repeated."],"references":["Bailey S, Wallwork B. Differentiating between benign and malignant thyroid nodules. Australian Journal of General Practitioners. 2021;47(11):770-774.","Lee J, Harris A, Khafagi F. Thyroid scans. Australian Family Physician. 2012;41(8):584-586."]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"20603"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"2652"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"20603","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/20603"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2023-05-08T15:25:05+09:30","updatedAt":"2024-10-01T15:18:22+09:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"2652"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"35775"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"4","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/4"},"attributes":{"emoji":"\ud83c\udf6c","name":"Endocrinology","synonyms":[],"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":"2024-11-21T09:49:43+10:30"},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"1"}},"heading":{"data":{"type":"tagHeadings","id":"1"}}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"65","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/65"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Investigations","synonyms":null,"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"5"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"72","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/72"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Graduating","synonyms":null,"description":"Only suitable for a graduating medical student at the end of their degree","position":1,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"6"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"76","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/76"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Level 